{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775620395784,"sessionID":"ses_294c9a59bffeejOnw7iheHHCCR","part":{"id":"prt_d6b38f207001rvj4v4vkijumFB","messageID":"msg_d6b38e3bb00120xCDrrWMqQIfd","sessionID":"ses_294c9a59bffeejOnw7iheHHCCR","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_bdrk_01QzytLbxkkcQ7D2b19qeSnT","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"bash /Users/ericmjl/github/marimo-pair-benchmark/.agents/skills/marimo-pair/scripts/execute-code.sh --port 2719 --session s_n5dyw4 <<'PYEOF'\nimport marimo._code_mode as cm\n\nasync with cm.get_context() as ctx:\n    md_rank = ctx.create_cell(\"mo.md(r'''## Rank Positions by Activity\\n\\nWe rank positions two ways to identify the most promising mutation sites. First, we rank by the average value of the mean column across all mutant residues at each position — this highlights positions that are broadly tolerant to or improved by substitution. Second, we rank by the top (maximum) value of the mean column at each position — this highlights positions where at least one substitution produced a strong effect. We take the top 20 from each ranking for comparison.''')\")\n    ctx.run_cell(md_rank)\n\n    code_rank = ctx.create_cell(\n        \"# Rank positions by average mean activity\\n\"\n        \"pos_avg_mean = df_single.groupby('position')['mean'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\"\n        \"top20_avg = set(pos_avg_mean.head(20).index.tolist())\\n\"\n        \"\\n\"\n        \"# Rank positions by top (max) mean activity\\n\"\n        \"pos_max_mean = df_single.groupby('position')['mean'].max().sort_values(ascending=False)\\n\"\n        \"top20_max = set(pos_max_mean.head(20).index.tolist())\\n\"\n        \"\\n\"\n        \"print('Top 20 positions by AVERAGE mean:')\\n\"\n        \"print(pos_avg_mean.head(20).to_string())\\n\"\n        \"print()\\n\"\n        \"print('Top 20 positions by MAX mean:')\\n\"\n        \"print(pos_max_mean.head(20).to_string())\\n\"\n        \"print()\\n\"\n        \"print(f'Overlap: {len(top20_avg & top20_max)} positions appear in both top-20 lists')\\n\"\n        \"print(f'Positions in both: {sorted(top20_avg & top20_max)}')\\n\"\n        \"print(f'Only in avg top-20: {sorted(top20_avg - top20_max)}')\\n\"\n        \"print(f'Only in max top-20: {sorted(top20_max - top20_avg)}')\"\n    )\n    ctx.run_cell(code_rank)\nPYEOF","description":"Create position ranking cells"},"output":"Top 20 positions by AVERAGE mean:\nposition\n243    0.294016\n156    0.275805\n212    0.252353\n159    0.250386\n242    0.211830\n6      0.206072\n155    0.196761\n247    0.196451\n117    0.196220\n218    0.190786\n154    0.188900\n118    0.188226\n216    0.182878\n114    0.181352\n303    0.176979\n220    0.175190\n304    0.169702\n215    0.168819\n160    0.165982\n188    0.164276\n\nTop 20 positions by MAX mean:\nposition\n296    0.711704\n220    0.677792\n154    0.583321\n175    0.539144\n218    0.518948\n243    0.500955\n57     0.492574\n259    0.487927\n26     0.469950\n247    0.468804\n212    0.466766\n33     0.445350\n6      0.437524\n159    0.426574\n156    0.425329\n177    0.422666\n160    0.419964\n242    0.418833\n189    0.407132\n71     0.369652\n\nOverlap: 11 positions appear in both top-20 lists\nPositions in both: [6, 154, 156, 159, 160, 212, 218, 220, 242, 243, 247]\nOnly in avg top-20: [114, 117, 118, 155, 188, 215, 216, 303, 304]\nOnly in max top-20: [26, 33, 57, 71, 175, 177, 189, 259, 296]\ncreated and ran cell 'WWaV'\ncreated and ran cell 'mzAg'\n\n","metadata":{"output":"Top 20 positions by AVERAGE mean:\nposition\n243    0.294016\n156    0.275805\n212    0.252353\n159    0.250386\n242    0.211830\n6      0.206072\n155    0.196761\n247    0.196451\n117    0.196220\n218    0.190786\n154    0.188900\n118    0.188226\n216    0.182878\n114    0.181352\n303    0.176979\n220    0.175190\n304    0.169702\n215    0.168819\n160    0.165982\n188    0.164276\n\nTop 20 positions by MAX mean:\nposition\n296    0.711704\n220    0.677792\n154    0.583321\n175    0.53914